Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Cut @broccoli{1} into
bite-size pieces if necessary.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of
@cooking oil{2%tablespoon}, half the @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and
@pepper{} . Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet
then).

While potatoes roast, heat a large drizzle of oil in a large, preferably
#nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and
cook, stirring, until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. Wipe
out pan.

> TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert),
> you can get started on them now!

Once potatoes have roasted 10 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully toss
broccoli on opposite side of sheet with a drizzle of oil, @onion powder{1%tablespoon},
salt, and pepper. Return to top rack and roast, until veggies are browned and
tender, ~{15-20%minutes} more. (For 4 servings, transfer baking sheet with
potatoes to middle rack; toss broccoli as instructed on a separate baking
sheet and roast on top rack.)

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all
over with remaining Fry Seasoning, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for panko over medium-high heat. Add chicken
and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small pot{} over
medium heat. Whisk in @cream cheese{4%tablespoon} until melted, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Slowly whisk in 1/4 cup water (1/2 cup for 4) until no lumps remain. Sprinkle
in @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} and @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}. Cook, whisking,
until melted and smooth, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer
to a #small serving bowl{}.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, add more water a splash at a time until sauce
> reaches desired consistency.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Serve chicken, potatoes, broccoli, toasted panko, cheese sauce, and
@buttermilk ranch dressing{1.5%ounce} family style so everyone can build their
own plate.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.